      A: 'Signal 1 alone is NOT sufficient for T-cell activation — it is specifically INSUFFICIENT without Signal 2. The two-signal model was established precisely because T cells encountering antigen without costimulation become tolerant (anergic), not activated. This is why grafts and tumors sometimes evade immune responses by downregulating B7 molecules.',
      C: 'Signal 1 without Signal 2 does not immediately trigger apoptosis via Fas–FasL (activation-induced cell death). AICD occurs in ACTIVATED T cells that are repeatedly stimulated — it is a mechanism for terminating immune responses after activation. Anergy (functional silencing) is the outcome of Signal 1 without Signal 2, not immediate apoptosis.',
